org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.definitions

Class StyleDefinition

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.definitions.DefinitionBase
      • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.definitions.MetadataDefinitionBase
        • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.definitions.StyleDefinition
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDefinition, IDocumentableDefinition, IMetadataDefinition, IStyleDefinition, IDefinitionSet

    public class StyleDefinition
extends MetadataDefinitionBase
implements IStyleDefinition
    Instances of this class represent definitions of MXML styles in the symbol table.

    MXML styles are defined by [Style] metadata on ActionScript class declarations.

    After a style definition is in the symbol table, it should always be accessed through the read-only IStyleDefinition interface.

      • getNode

        public IStyleTagNode getNode()
        Description copied from interface: IDefinition
        Returns the IDefinitionNode from which this definition was created, if the definition came from the AST for a source file.

        This method may require the AST to be reloaded or regenerated and therefore may be slow.

        More specific definition interfaces such as IClassDefinition redeclare this method to return a more specific node interface such as IClassNode.

        Specified by:
        getNode in interface IDefinition
        Specified by:
        getNode in interface IStyleDefinition
